# Supabase Declarative Schema & Migrations

## Directory Structure

- `supabase/schemas/*.sql` — source of truth; declare the desired final state of all DB entities (DDL only)
- `supabase/migrations/` — auto-generated only; never hand-edit (except for known caveats)
- `src/types/database.ts` — auto-generated; never hand-edit
- New schema files must be registered in `schema_paths` in `supabase/config.toml`
- Schema files run in lexicographic order — name files to enforce dependency order (e.g. `01_employees.sql` before `02_managers.sql`)

## Workflow

Always follow this order when making schema changes:

```bash
# 1. Edit supabase/schemas/*.sql (DDL only)

# 2. Stop local environment before diffing
supabase stop

# 3. Generate migration
pnpm run create <descriptive_name>
# → runs: supabase db diff -f <name>
# → creates: supabase/migrations/<timestamp>_<name>.sql

# 4. Review the generated migration file carefully (watch for data loss)

# 5. Apply locally and regenerate TypeScript types
pnpm run migrate
# → runs: supabase db push --local --include-all && pnpm run types

# 6. Deploy to production
pnpm run migrate:production
# → runs: supabase db push --include-all
```

## Rollback

1. Revert the relevant `supabase/schemas/*.sql` files to the desired state
2. Run `pnpm run create <rollback_name>` to generate a down migration
3. Review carefully — rollback SQL is often destructive

## What Goes Where

| Entity | Location |
|---|---|
| `CREATE TABLE`, `ALTER TABLE`, `CREATE INDEX`, `CREATE FUNCTION`, `CREATE VIEW`, RLS policies | `supabase/schemas/` |
| `storage.buckets` rows and `storage.objects` RLS policies | `supabase/schemas/rls.sql` (or alongside other RLS) — if these exist only in old migrations, `db diff` may spuriously emit `DROP POLICY` |
| `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE` (seed data) | `supabase/seeders/` |
| Entities `migra` cannot diff (see caveats) | `supabase/migrations/` directly |

## Known Caveats — Use Manual Migration Files for These

`migra` cannot diff the following; add them directly as versioned migration files:

- **DML**: `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE`
- **View ownership**: grants, `SECURITY INVOKER`, materialized views, altering column type on a view
- **RLS**: `ALTER POLICY` statements, column privileges
- **Other**: schema privileges, comments, partitions, `ALTER PUBLICATION ... ADD TABLE`, `CREATE DOMAIN`, duplicate grants from default privileges

## Hard Rules

- Never edit migration files directly (except for known caveats above)
- Never manually edit `src/types/database.ts`
- Always append new columns to the end of table definitions (prevents messy diffs on views/enums)
- Always run `supabase stop` before generating a diff
- Always add new schema files to `schema_paths` in `supabase/config.toml` before diffing
